# ── IdeaForge configuration ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# With the free-tier group unset, the app runs in bring-your-own-key mode and
# costs you $0. The free tier turns ON only when ALL FIVE required vars below
# are set — missing any one means BYO-only (safe by default). Turnstile is now
# REQUIRED for the free tier (not optional).

# ── LOW-COST PILOT RECIPE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Real cost per AI call on claude-sonnet-5 (framework prompt + Korean output):
# roughly $0.02-0.05. A full visitor journey (Step 2 generate + Step 3
# evaluate) = 2 calls ≈ $0.04-0.10. At the defaults below (2/IP/day, 40/day
# global), worst case if the daily cap is fully used every single day of the
# month is ≈ $36-60/mo — but the numbers below are a same-day circuit
# breaker, not the actual budget. The REAL ceiling is step 1:
#
# 1) Server key that powers free runs. In the Anthropic Console, create a
#    DEDICATED workspace (not your main one), set a hard MONTHLY SPEND CAP
#    there — $10-15 is plenty for a pilot — then generate the key from that
#    workspace. That cap is your guaranteed worst case no matter what happens
#    below; nothing in this app can spend past it.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# 2) Rate-limit store (Upstash Redis, free tier is enough). Sign up at
#    upstash.com, create a Redis database, copy the REST URL + token. Quota
#    keys reset on the KST calendar day.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# 3) Cloudflare Turnstile (REQUIRED for free tier, free product). Add a site
#    at dash.cloudflare.com/?to=/:account/turnstile, mode "Managed", copy the
#    site key (public) and secret key.
NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=

# 4) Flip the "free to try" banner copy on (set to 1 only once 1–3 are live).
NEXT_PUBLIC_FREE_TIER=

# 5) Free-tier caps. Defaults are sized for a low-traffic pilot:
#    - 2/IP/day = exactly one full generate+evaluate pass per person per day.
#      (Not 1 — capping at 1 strands a visitor right at Step 3, the payoff,
#      after they've already invested in Step 1.)
#    - 40/day global = about 20 unique people fully trying it in a day.
#    Raise FREE_RUNS_GLOBAL_PER_DAY once you've watched real usage and are
#    comfortable with the actual daily spend it produces.
FREE_RUNS_PER_IP_PER_DAY=2
FREE_RUNS_GLOBAL_PER_DAY=40

# 6) Canonical site URL for metadata/OG (optional; defaults to the prod domain).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
